# Agent performance (Contextual Maestro)

This repo is small (~200 source files) when ignores are respected. Lag usually comes from indexing `node_modules`, `.next`, or `.venv`, or from broad searches.

## Do

- Rely on `.cursorignore` / `.gitignore` — do not read or search under `client/node_modules/`, `client/.next/`, or `server/.venv/`.
- Prefer targeted `Grep` / `Glob` / single-file `Read` over listing whole trees.
- Scope work to `client/` or `server/` when possible.
- Run one dev service at a time if the machine feels slow (Postgres in Docker + either API or UI).

## Avoid

- `@`-mentioning the whole repo or `node_modules`.
- Re-indexing by opening huge generated folders.
- Long parallel shell + browser + docker unless needed for QA.
- Reading lockfiles (`bun.lock`) unless debugging dependencies.

## Stack reminders

- API: `server/` (FastAPI, port 8000)
- UI: `client/` (Next.js, port 3000)
- DB: Docker Postgres on host port 5433
